The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Aug. 11: Finance minister Pranab Mukherjee has set a new direct tax collection target for the current fiscal, revising it upward to Rs 4 lakh crore, up Rs 30,000 crore over the budget estimates. The Centre will release the draft of the direct taxes code, which seeks to simplify taxation structure, for public discussion tomorrow.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 11: Tata Steel has reduced prices of some of its products, expecially those consumed by the construction sector. We have reduced prices of long steel products by Rs 1,000-1,500 a tonne in line with the current market trend, a Tata Steel spokesperson said.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 11: Deputy US trade representative Demetrios Marantis today met commerce minister Anand Sharma. He is believed to have discussed ways of resolving differences over the Doha round of world trade talks.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 11: The Reserve Bank today asked the public to verify credentials before dealing with entities promising loans, saying there were cases where such lenders disappeared after taking the processing fees.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 11: Toyota is evaluating the option of introducing a diesel version of its small car to be launched in the Indian market by 2011.                                                                                                                           
